      • doubleArrayReport

        public static java.lang.String doubleArrayReport(java.lang.String[] values,
                                 double[] array)
        Reports an array of doubles to the console within a supplied text. In the text use 'xx.xxx' to set the desired decimal places for each of the values in the array. The will be written in order. Decimal place in 'xx.xx' is not required, although to identify a number to write use at least two x ('xx').
        Parameters:
        values - The text with generic formmated numbers xxxx.xxx...
        array - The array with the values.
        Returns:
        The formatted text.

      • formatAsFortran

        public static java.lang.String formatAsFortran(java.lang.String[] val,
                               java.lang.String format,
                               boolean fillBefore)
        Formats a set of values in a Fortran style way.
        Parameters:
        val - The set of values.
        format - The format to apply, for example '1x, i2, 2f5.4, a3'.
        fillBefore - True to fill with blank spaces before the values in case the field is longer than the length of the value. False will fill with blanks after the field value. True is used commonly so that values will be aligned to the right, and decimal point always at the same place.
        Returns:
        The formatted output.
